The Vice President of the United States, Mike Pence, delivered a speech in York, Pennsylvania, highlighting the economic achievements of the Trump administration and urging Congress to pass the United States-Mexico-Canada Agreement (USMCA). Pence emphasized the job growth and wage increases that have occurred under the current administration, attributing them to policies such as tax cuts, deregulation, and energy expansion. He also praised the resilience and hard work of American manufacturing workers and expressed optimism for the future of the industry. Pence called on the public to support the USMCA and urged them to make their voices heard by contacting their representatives in Congress. He also addressed the issue of illegal immigration, emphasizing the need for Congress and Mexico to take action to secure the southern border. Pence concluded his speech by reiterating his commitment to continue fighting for policies that promote economic growth and make America prosperous.